dcterms:description: The CS dataset consists of battery usage data from the Center for Advanced Life Cycle Engineering (CALCE) of the University of Maryland, specifically focusing on batteries with the same polar materials and charging/discharging processes.
dcterms:title: CS Dataset

dcterms:creator: B. Bole
C. Kulkarni
M. Daigle
dcterms:description: The CX2 dataset includes battery usage data from CALCE, focusing on batteries with different capacity ratings but similar charging and discharging processes.
dcterms:title: CX2 Dataset

dcterms:creator: W. He
N. Williard
M. Osterman
M. Pecht
dcterms:description: The NASA RW dataset consists of battery data from the NASA Ames Prognostics Center of Excellence, focusing on random walk discharging cycles of lithium-ion batteries.
dcterms:title: NASA RW Dataset

dcterms:creator: Y. Xing
E. W. Ma
K.-L. Tsui
M. Pecht
dcterms:description: The NASA RW dataset is also referenced in the context of an ensemble model for predicting the remaining useful performance of lithium-ion batteries.
dcterms:title: NASA RW Dataset (additional reference)
